{"parentUuid":"fc758320-dfa0-4a26-8eb4-2d96ab8e170a","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"S:\\01_Repos\\BeFirst_Docs","sessionId":"738a70de-a593-468d-9535-0a1a31be5d45","version":"2.1.41","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a5d5114","slug":"cozy-prancing-cray","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_01VV5YjiqXHMCAmrCzLbjT2t","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Here's the exact markup for the first 3 form fields in the General tab:\n\n## Form Field Markup (Lines 32-58)\n\n```html\n<!-- Field 1: CellName -->\n<div class=\"input-group mb-3\">\n  <div class=\"input-group-prepend\">\n    <span class=\"input-group-text\">\n      @Html.LabelFor(y => y.CellName, new { @class = \"m-0 fs-14\" })\n    </span>\n  </div>\n  @Html.TextBoxFor(y => y.CellName, new { @class = \"form-control\" })\n</div>\n\n<!-- Field 2: Facility_Name -->\n<div class=\"input-group mb-3\">\n  <div class=\"input-group-prepend\">\n    <span class=\"input-group-text\">\n      @Html.LabelFor(y => y.Facility_Name, new { @class = \"m-0 fs-14\" })\n    </span>\n  </div>\n  @Html.DropDownListFor(y => y.Facility_Key, (IEnumerable<SelectListItem>)Model.FacilityList, new { @class = \"form-control\" })\n</div>\n\n<!-- Field 3: CellTypeID -->\n<div class=\"input-group mb-3\">\n  <div class=\"input-group-prepend\">\n    <span class=\"input-group-text\">\n      @Html.LabelFor(y => y.CellTypeID, new { @class = \"m-0 fs-14\" })\n    </span>\n  </div>\n  @Html.DropDownListFor(y => y.CellTypeID, (IEnumerable<SelectListItem>)celltypelist, new { @class = \"form-control\" })\n</div>\n```\n\n## Key Spacing Pattern\n\n**Answer to your question:** They use **`mb-3` on every `.input-group` container** - NOT `pt-3` on `uk-grid`.\n\n**Pattern characteristics:**\n- ✅ **Bootstrap input groups** (not UIkit grid for fields)\n- ✅ **Bottom margin only**: `mb-3` class on each `.input-group`\n- ✅ **No top padding**: No `pt-3` used\n- ✅ **Consistent label styling**: `m-0 fs-14` (no margin, font-size 14px)\n- ✅ **No field wrapping containers**: Fields stack directly with margin-bottom spacing\n\nThis is a simpler pattern than the Station form (which used `uk-grid pt-3`). The Cells form uses straightforward Bootstrap input groups with bottom margin spacing."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3708,"cache_read_input_tokens":22632,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3708,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011Cb33SV7rmYahWMDDBK4QZ","type":"assistant","uuid":"d63ebfe6-f4d5-4ba7-8842-d562d2fd27ee","timestamp":"2026-05-14T19:50:56.104Z"}
